<item>
            <title>[DERBY-2486] Control a sort just through SortController and remove concept of a long sort identifier</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2486</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A sort is obtained through TransactionController.openSort() which returns a long, this is then used with various methods on TransactionController to get a SortController, get the scans against the sort and drop the sort.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not a natural OO style of programming, instead the open should return the SortController and then all actions on the sort including dropping be methods on SortController.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would be cleaner and remove the logic in RAMTransaction that tries to re-uses long sort identifiers.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
